WEBVTT

00:03.003 --> 00:05.255
GREAT DRAGON:
In a land of myth and a time of magic...

00:05.422 --> 00:10.469
...the destiny of a great kingdom
rests on the shoulders of a young man.

00:10.636 --> 00:14.223
His name: Merlin.

00:22.397 --> 00:24.107
There's a chill in the air tonight.

00:24.274 --> 00:26.151
[MARY CHUCKLES]

00:28.237 --> 00:31.323
-What?
-You say that every night.

00:31.532 --> 00:33.033
[CHUCKLES]

00:33.450 --> 00:36.411
-Do I now?
-Only for the last 30 years.

00:36.578 --> 00:37.871
[JOHN CHUCKLES]

00:38.038 --> 00:40.290
Stop your fussing and come to bed.

00:40.457 --> 00:42.543
[MAN SCREAMS NEARBY]

00:46.004 --> 00:47.422
John.

00:47.881 --> 00:50.050
Don't go outside. I'm begging you.

00:50.217 --> 00:52.302
It's my duty. I'm the elder of this village.

00:52.469 --> 00:53.554
John, please--

00:53.720 --> 00:58.100
Lock the door behind me.
Let no one in. No one. Do you hear?

01:07.442 --> 01:09.486
[HORSE WHINNIES IN DISTANCE]

01:14.199 --> 01:16.159
[CHILD CRYING]

01:33.010 --> 01:34.845
[CLATTERING]

01:36.221 --> 01:38.223
[CREATURE HISSING]

01:40.767 --> 01:43.103
[DOOR CREAKING AND THUDDING]

01:57.159 --> 01:58.577
[GASPS]

02:03.290 --> 02:04.374
Aldrif?

02:06.543 --> 02:08.169
[CREATURE HISSING]

02:08.919 --> 02:10.505
Hello?

02:11.048 --> 02:13.050
Is there anybody there?

02:15.218 --> 02:16.762
[HISSES]

02:56.051 --> 02:57.678
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

03:02.724 --> 03:04.184
Gwen?

03:04.351 --> 03:05.394
Mary.

03:05.560 --> 03:07.104
| was told I might find you here.

03:07.270 --> 03:08.355
Mary.

03:09.690 --> 03:11.483
What a wonderful surprise.

03:11.650 --> 03:13.276
| hope I'm not interrupting anything.

03:13.443 --> 03:17.072
No, no, not at all.
What brings you to Camelot?

03:18.240 --> 03:19.866
| don't want to trouble you, Gwen.

03:20.033 --> 03:23.704
John and I--
| know we haven't seen you for many years...

03:23.870 --> 03:26.039
...but there was no else we could turn to.

03:26.206 --> 03:27.416
What is it?

03:28.250 --> 03:31.294
We're just-- We're just so scared.

03:31.962 --> 03:33.672
Oh, Mary.

03:35.799 --> 03:38.969
Guinevere informs me that you live
in Longstead in the Feorre Mountains.

03:39.136 --> 03:40.512
Is that right?

03:41.012 --> 03:42.681
That's right, sire.

03:45.016 --> 03:48.979
Our village-- We're blighted by a sickness.

03:49.396 --> 03:51.732
Three good men it has taken now.

03:51.898 --> 03:54.443
We have no physician, sire.

03:54.609 --> 03:56.445
It is beyond our understanding.

03:57.529 --> 03:58.905
| see.

04:01.408 --> 04:02.743
Forgive me.

04:02.909 --> 04:05.871
| have no right to bring
such a small matter before the king.

04:06.037 --> 04:07.914
You have every right.

04:08.915 --> 04:11.418
It is my responsibility
to protect the people of this kingdom...

04:11.585 --> 04:13.044
...whoever they may be.

04:13.211 --> 04:14.588
You'll help us?

04:15.046 --> 04:16.339
I'll do whatever I can.

04:17.841 --> 04:19.341
Thank you.

04:19.760 --> 04:22.971
GAIUS: This is the fourth case
of sweating sickness I've seen today.

04:23.138 --> 04:27.559
In normal circumstances, I'd be happy
to travel to this village to investigate, but--

04:27.726 --> 04:31.730
-Of course. I understand.
-Might I make a suggestion, sire?

04:34.191 --> 04:37.152
Why not send Merlin in my place?

04:39.863 --> 04:42.407
-Merlin?
-He has a knowledge of the healing arts.

04:42.574 --> 04:46.203
If the diagnosis is straightforward,
he can prescribe a remedy, I'm sure.

04:46.369 --> 04:49.372
-And what if it isn't?
-Then he can bring his findings to me.

04:50.040 --> 04:51.416
Findings?

04:51.583 --> 04:54.711
Merlin can't find his own backside
most of the time.

04:54.878 --> 04:57.964
| think he's capable of much more
than you imagine, sire.

05:01.009 --> 05:04.596
You really think he'll be able
to handle the responsibility?

05:05.305 --> 05:07.516
Yes, sire, I do.

05:12.521 --> 05:14.815
Do you really think I can do this, Gaius?

05:14.981 --> 05:16.024
| know you can.

05:16.191 --> 05:18.902
I'm not a physician. I don't have anything
like the knowledge you do.

05:19.069 --> 05:21.029
You've been working for me
for many years, Merlin.

05:21.196 --> 05:23.532
| suspect you know more
than you think you do.

05:23.698 --> 05:26.701
| just do what you tell me to do.
| don't have to make the decisions myself.

05:26.868 --> 05:28.912
These people will be putting
their lives in my hands.

05:29.079 --> 05:31.748
| put my life in your hands every day, Merlin.

05:31.915 --> 05:34.209
As does Arthur and Gwen
and all of Camelot...

05:34.376 --> 05:36.294
...though they may not know it.

05:36.503 --> 05:39.923
You're the one who holds
the fate of this kingdom in the balance.

05:41.174 --> 05:44.177
But that's different.
That doesn't require a lifetime of learning, just--

05:44.344 --> 05:47.180
Intelligence, courage, compassion.

05:47.347 --> 05:48.682
[SIGHS]

05:50.934 --> 05:52.936
All I know is...

05:53.103 --> 05:55.647
...| have every faith in you.

06:05.657 --> 06:06.700
GAIUS:
Merlin.

06:07.784 --> 06:11.204
Before you go, you'll need this.

06:13.874 --> 06:16.293
Oh, I can't take that, Gaius.
That's your medicine bag.

06:16.459 --> 06:20.297
Don't worry.
I've got plenty of spare supplies.

06:29.306 --> 06:30.348
Thanks, Gaius.

06:32.976 --> 06:34.019
Are you ready?

06:35.478 --> 06:37.105
As I'll ever be.

06:59.002 --> 07:01.087
My village lies at the foot
of those mountains.

07:05.592 --> 07:07.302
With luck, we should be there by nightfall.

07:30.158 --> 07:31.576
John.

07:31.910 --> 07:33.453
It's good to see you.

07:33.620 --> 07:35.288
We came as quickly as we could.

07:35.455 --> 07:38.458
Words cannot express our gratitude, Gwen.

07:40.043 --> 07:43.713
-Where's Gaius?
-I'm sorry. He was needed in Camelot...

07:43.880 --> 07:46.341
...but I will help in any way that I can.

07:47.342 --> 07:51.721
We're living in fear for our lives.
We need a skilled physician, not a boy.

07:51.888 --> 07:53.848
His name is Merlin.

07:56.059 --> 07:58.812
He was appointed acting physician
by King Arthur himself.

08:01.314 --> 08:02.357
Where are they?

08:10.699 --> 08:12.367
[FIRE CRACKLING]

08:20.500 --> 08:24.129
They're alive, but only just.
How long have they been like this?

08:24.587 --> 08:25.964
Two or three days.

08:26.131 --> 08:29.968
We've tried to feed them, keep them warm,
but nothing seems to make any difference.

08:30.135 --> 08:31.970
GWEN: And you've no idea
what happened to them?

08:32.136 --> 08:36.307
No. It just strikes suddenly, without warning.

08:36.933 --> 08:39.269
Well, we need to stimulate the blood flow.

08:39.894 --> 08:41.730
A poultice of patchouli oil should work...

08:41.895 --> 08:44.858
...and a tincture of belladonna
to stimulate the heart.

08:45.025 --> 08:47.944
Will it cure them? Will it bring them back?

08:48.111 --> 08:49.446
Let's see what the morning brings.

08:49.612 --> 08:51.906
Right now we need hot water
and plenty of blankets.

08:56.202 --> 08:58.038
[DOOR CLOSES]

08:58.455 --> 09:00.665
[SPEAKS MAGIC WORDS]

09:15.722 --> 09:17.640
[CREATURE HISSING NEARBY]

09:46.419 --> 09:47.670
[HISSING CONTINUES]

10:01.601 --> 10:05.146
-Gwaine!
-Sorry. Call of nature.

10:05.313 --> 10:06.523
| could have killed you.

10:06.689 --> 10:08.525
With a fishing rod?

10:09.150 --> 10:12.278
"Sir Gwaine was slain with a fishing rod."

10:12.487 --> 10:14.072
[CHUCKLES]

10:14.239 --> 10:17.826
That's the stuff of legends, eh? Whoa-ho.

10:17.992 --> 10:19.994
[GWAINE CHUCKLES]

10:20.703 --> 10:22.330
[HISSING AND RATTLING]

10:39.472 --> 10:41.224
| barely feel a pulse.

10:49.232 --> 10:50.733
How are they?

10:57.407 --> 10:59.492
I'm afraid the treatments have had no effect.

11:00.034 --> 11:01.244
You mean they're dying.

11:03.413 --> 11:05.081
I'm sorry.

11:06.541 --> 11:09.210
There's something at work here
that I don't understand.

11:09.377 --> 11:11.546
Are you suggesting sorcery?

11:12.589 --> 11:14.674
That's possible, yes.

11:14.841 --> 11:16.176
| feared as much.

11:16.342 --> 11:18.386
The other night, when I found Aldrif...

11:19.804 --> 11:22.932
...| felt a-- A presence.

11:23.808 --> 11:25.977
An evil in the air.

11:30.023 --> 11:31.357
We need to get back to Gaius.

11:33.443 --> 11:34.485
Only he can explain this.

11:59.093 --> 12:00.553
Whoa.

12:03.848 --> 12:06.184
Dismount and muzzle your horses.

12:06.351 --> 12:08.311
Not a sound, any of you.

12:20.573 --> 12:22.242
[MEN LAUGHING]

12:23.534 --> 12:24.702
Bandits?

12:24.869 --> 12:26.871
-Looks like it.
-We'll skirt their camp.

12:27.038 --> 12:29.624
With any luck,
we'll reach the plain unnoticed.

12:29.791 --> 12:30.833
Over there.

12:32.085 --> 12:33.169
[MEN LAUGHING]

12:36.839 --> 12:39.092
[GWAINE YELLS]
[BANDIT GRUNTS]

12:39.300 --> 12:40.760
[ALL GRUNTING]

13:25.638 --> 13:26.806
PERCIVAL:
Over here.

13:37.233 --> 13:38.443
Looks like we were too late.

13:40.194 --> 13:41.404
MERLIN: No, she's--
-Aah!

13:41.571 --> 13:45.241
Hey! Hey! Hey! It's all right.

13:45.908 --> 13:49.162
It's all right. We're knights of Camelot.

13:50.038 --> 13:51.080
You're safe now.

13:52.081 --> 13:53.541
You're safe.

13:55.585 --> 13:57.420
Here.

13:57.587 --> 13:59.213
My name's Gwen. What's yours?

14:01.966 --> 14:03.676
Lamia.

14:04.052 --> 14:05.386
My name is Lamia.

14:05.887 --> 14:07.555
What happened to you, Lamia?

14:10.808 --> 14:13.644
| was traveling home
when the bandits took me.

14:13.811 --> 14:15.521
[SOBBING]

14:18.274 --> 14:20.693
Your hands. Did they do this to you?

14:20.860 --> 14:22.362
-Let me clean them--
-No! No!

14:27.575 --> 14:28.743
Are you strong enough to ride?

14:34.499 --> 14:37.919
Then let's get out of here before they return.

14:55.228 --> 14:57.438
We'll be safe here till the morning.

15:05.321 --> 15:06.364
Here.

15:06.531 --> 15:07.573
[GASPS]

15:07.740 --> 15:09.575
Hey. Get away from her, Merlin.

15:14.163 --> 15:15.706
And stay away.

15:16.290 --> 15:18.292
Merlin, he didn't mean it.

15:18.459 --> 15:20.628
They're just tired. That's all.

15:25.007 --> 15:27.176
[WOLF HOWLING IN DISTANCE]

15:32.056 --> 15:33.808
[LAMIA WHIMPERING]

16:01.586 --> 16:03.337
[SOBBING]

16:10.136 --> 16:12.305
PERCIVAL:
Shh.

16:16.017 --> 16:17.602
Don't worry.

16:18.352 --> 16:20.688
No harm can come to you now.

16:28.196 --> 16:30.072
[HISSING]

16:32.950 --> 16:34.619
[BRANCH SNAPS]

16:37.747 --> 16:38.789
Sorry.

16:43.669 --> 16:44.962
Would you like some water?

16:56.516 --> 16:58.434
ARTHUR:
It's been two days.

16:58.601 --> 17:00.061
They should be back by now.

17:00.228 --> 17:02.021
There must be some delay
at Longstead, sire.

17:02.188 --> 17:03.940
If there was a delay,
they would have sent word.

17:04.106 --> 17:06.108
Then it must be the bridge
is down at Brechfa River.

17:06.275 --> 17:09.237
No, I already checked.
A patrol passed through there yesterday.

17:09.403 --> 17:11.948
Well, should I send some scouts out
to search for them?

17:12.114 --> 17:13.449
Gaius, is your work done here?

17:13.616 --> 17:17.161
Yes, sire. I'm satisfied the sweating sickness
has all but passed.

17:17.328 --> 17:19.872
Then we leave for Longstead at first light.

17:38.891 --> 17:39.934
GWEN:
Would you like--?

17:41.811 --> 17:43.437
I'll just put it here.

17:50.820 --> 17:54.907
She still won't eat. No appetite at all.

17:55.074 --> 17:56.200
Poor girl.

17:56.367 --> 17:59.662
Pack your bags.
We ride east with the rising sun.

17:59.829 --> 18:02.206
Wait. East?

18:03.624 --> 18:04.750
Camelot lies west of here.

18:04.917 --> 18:07.712
Lamia has asked that we take her home.

18:07.878 --> 18:10.965
-No, we need to get Gaius.
-Gaius can wait.

18:13.718 --> 18:15.553
We were sent to help
the people of Longstead.

18:15.720 --> 18:18.931
-Their lives depend on us.
-You dare to question our judgment?

18:20.683 --> 18:22.727
You are not a knight.

18:23.144 --> 18:26.480
You're not even a physician.
You're nothing but a servant.

18:27.064 --> 18:29.400
Please! Listen, Merlin's right.
We have to get back--

18:29.567 --> 18:32.403
Stay out of this, Gwen.
It's none of your business.

18:43.748 --> 18:45.333
[SCOFFS]

19:21.494 --> 19:23.663
-Is anything wrong, sire?
-Listen.

19:25.498 --> 19:28.459
No birdsong. Nothing.

19:29.960 --> 19:31.295
Sire!

20:10.167 --> 20:12.878
Does anything strike you
as odd about these bodies?

20:13.045 --> 20:15.423
Yes, sire. There's not a mark on them.

20:15.589 --> 20:17.800
-Not so much as a scratch.
AGRAVAINE: Over here, my lord.

20:20.261 --> 20:22.263
Southron slave traders by the looks of it.

20:23.180 --> 20:25.975
AGRAVAINE: What were they transporting,
some kind of an animal?

20:27.977 --> 20:30.479
No. These marks were made by humans.

20:31.063 --> 20:35.735
And whoever they were,
they did anything they had to to get out.

20:36.736 --> 20:38.738
[MAN GROANING]

20:43.617 --> 20:45.202
Can he be treated?

20:46.412 --> 20:49.999
| could try, sire. But I'll need time
and somewhere to work.

20:50.166 --> 20:52.001
He comes with us.

20:52.168 --> 20:53.836
We'll make Longstead in a matter of hours.

21:06.182 --> 21:08.684
-Why don't you watch what you're doing?
-Watch your damn tongue.

21:08.851 --> 21:11.854
-You'd do well to learn some manners.
-Nothing I can learn from you.

21:12.021 --> 21:13.439
-We'll see about that.
-Enough!

21:14.899 --> 21:16.066
What's got into you?

21:19.153 --> 21:20.529
[GWAINE GRUNTS]

21:36.420 --> 21:37.713
Great!

21:37.880 --> 21:40.174
-Take him.
-I'll get the medicine bag.

21:41.258 --> 21:42.843
Come on.

21:46.722 --> 21:50.142
Spread out and speak to everyone.
Someone must know something.

21:51.185 --> 21:52.770
Did you speak to the village elder?

21:52.937 --> 21:55.981
-It seems they left yesterday morning.
-Where were they headed?

21:56.148 --> 21:57.942
Camelot, my lord.

21:59.527 --> 22:01.320
Something must have happened.

22:01.487 --> 22:03.489
We can't go after them tonight.

22:04.365 --> 22:06.367
Then we ride at dawn.
See that the men are prepared.

22:06.534 --> 22:07.952
Yes, sire.

22:09.745 --> 22:11.997
And they've been like this for four days?

22:12.164 --> 22:14.083
And each day, they grow weaker.

22:17.044 --> 22:18.379
Merlin is right.

22:19.171 --> 22:20.673
This is no ordinary illness.

22:22.258 --> 22:25.010
There is sorcery at work here.

22:26.595 --> 22:28.806
LEON:
That needle's the size of a spear.

22:31.350 --> 22:33.561
Well, I'm sorry. It's all I have.

22:33.727 --> 22:36.814
-Wait. Done.
-Thank you.

22:44.947 --> 22:47.700
Leon and Gwaine,
I've never known them to act like this.

22:47.867 --> 22:50.953
Elyan's the same. I hardly recognize him.

22:56.709 --> 22:58.961
| think it's something to do with her.

22:59.503 --> 23:01.213
-Lamia?
-The knights are like brothers...

23:01.380 --> 23:02.965
...yet they fight and quarrel like foes.

23:03.132 --> 23:05.134
It started the moment we found her.

23:05.301 --> 23:07.094
But look at her. She's just a girl.

23:07.261 --> 23:09.138
How could she affect them this way?

23:09.680 --> 23:11.515
Hmm.

23:12.641 --> 23:14.184
| don't know.

23:26.697 --> 23:28.032
ARTHUR:
Any luck with the Southron?

23:28.198 --> 23:32.077
I've done my best, sire.
His condition is perilous, but he lives.

23:32.244 --> 23:33.579
Was he able to tell us anything?

23:33.746 --> 23:36.206
He is a slave trader, as you suspected.

23:36.373 --> 23:38.334
They were traveling south with a girl.

23:39.126 --> 23:43.297
-Did he say what happened to them?
-He claims they fell under some kind of spell.

23:43.464 --> 23:45.883
Quarrels and fights broke out among them.

23:46.050 --> 23:48.886
They began to suspect the girl
of bewitching them.

23:49.762 --> 23:51.347
It seems they were right.

23:51.513 --> 23:52.848
Why? What happened?

23:53.015 --> 23:55.517
The girl escaped and killed them all but him.

23:56.352 --> 23:58.854
How is that possible? She's just one girl.

23:59.021 --> 24:00.564
Not a girl, sire.

24:00.731 --> 24:02.191
A lamia.

24:03.692 --> 24:06.528
-A lamia?
-A creature of magic.

24:07.446 --> 24:11.700
In their wars with the ancient kings,
the high priestesses of the old religion...

24:11.867 --> 24:15.746
...took the blood from a girl
and mingled it with that of a serpent.

24:16.246 --> 24:19.833
The creatures they created
had ferocious powers.

24:20.000 --> 24:25.297
They could control the mind of a man,
suck the life from him with a single embrace.

24:25.464 --> 24:28.342
Which is why none of the traders
had a mark on them.

24:28.509 --> 24:32.346
But the lamia proved more deadly
than their makers had ever imagined.

24:32.846 --> 24:38.310
They could transform at will
and become hideous monsters.

24:38.477 --> 24:40.354
[LAMIA HISSING]

24:49.071 --> 24:50.489
And they kept on killing, sire.

24:51.156 --> 24:52.282
They would not stop.

24:52.449 --> 24:55.536
So this girl, this creature,
is still out there somewhere.

24:56.495 --> 24:58.205
I'm afraid so, sire.

25:10.718 --> 25:12.344
[LEAVES RUSTLE]

25:15.472 --> 25:16.974
Forgive me.

25:18.017 --> 25:19.059
[SIGHS]

25:19.226 --> 25:21.228
| didn't mean to frighten you.

25:21.812 --> 25:23.022
| couldn't sleep.

25:24.690 --> 25:26.400
Nor could I.

25:28.569 --> 25:30.821
Then again, it is my job to stay awake.

25:33.032 --> 25:34.283
Don't be afraid.

25:37.745 --> 25:39.747
| won't hurt you.

25:45.210 --> 25:47.171
[HISSING]

26:08.734 --> 26:10.152
LEON:
Elyan?

26:10.611 --> 26:12.571
He was supposed to be on guard.

26:12.780 --> 26:14.698
He should have woken us long before now.
Elyan!

26:14.865 --> 26:16.116
Elyan!

26:16.283 --> 26:17.993
[GWEN SIGHS]

26:18.410 --> 26:19.953
Elyan!

26:20.120 --> 26:23.749
Gwen, stay with Lamia.
The rest of you, come with me.

26:23.916 --> 26:25.375
Spread out. Elyan!

26:28.045 --> 26:29.296
Don't worry.

26:30.089 --> 26:32.049
They'll find your brother soon enough.

26:32.257 --> 26:34.927
LEON:
Elyan! Elyan!

26:55.447 --> 26:57.241
Six horses.

26:58.075 --> 26:59.827
Riding east.

27:00.994 --> 27:02.913
The tracks are no more than a day old.

27:14.258 --> 27:16.885
GWEN:
Oh, God. Elyan!

27:17.052 --> 27:18.345
Oh. What happened to him?

27:18.512 --> 27:21.223
| don't know. We found him like this.

27:23.267 --> 27:24.518
Merlin.

27:25.269 --> 27:27.354
[WHISPERING]
She did this. I know she did.

27:30.149 --> 27:32.276
We need to get him back to Camelot now.

27:32.442 --> 27:36.155
| know this area.
There's a castle not far from here.

27:36.780 --> 27:39.116
We could take shelter there.
You could tend to your friend.

27:39.283 --> 27:41.785
LEON: Then lead the way.
-We don't need shelter. We need Gaius.

27:41.952 --> 27:44.121
-He's right.
-Silence! Both of you!

27:45.038 --> 27:48.584
You have no say in these matters.
You come with us or you stay here.

27:48.750 --> 27:50.043
It's up to you.

27:50.752 --> 27:52.045
Let's go.

28:09.188 --> 28:10.814
GWEN:
We could try reasoning with them...

28:10.981 --> 28:13.108
...tell them Lamia's responsible
for what's happening.

28:13.275 --> 28:16.612
They won't listen. You've seen how they are.
It's like they're under an enchantment.

28:16.778 --> 28:17.821
We have to do something.

28:17.988 --> 28:20.032
Arthur's our only hope now.
We've been gone too long.

28:20.199 --> 28:22.326
-He must know something's wrong.
-He'll never find us.

28:22.492 --> 28:24.369
We're in the middle of nowhere.

28:26.538 --> 28:28.624
We need to give him some help.

28:41.136 --> 28:44.097
-The tracks stop here.
-We could be wasting our time, sire.

28:44.264 --> 28:46.683
For all we know,
they could have gone back to Camelot already.

28:46.850 --> 28:52.898
No. Camelot lies west of here.
Tracks are heading east.

28:56.568 --> 28:58.320
Fan out. See what you can find.

29:03.158 --> 29:05.202
[FABRIC RIPS]

30:11.101 --> 30:12.811
LAMIA:
This way.

30:18.650 --> 30:20.068
This is madness, Percival.

30:20.235 --> 30:22.237
Elyan needs help.
You know nothing about this girl.

30:22.404 --> 30:24.823
You've no idea where she's taking you.

30:28.910 --> 30:30.746
You heard Sir Leon.

30:30.912 --> 30:32.998
We have no interest in your opinion.

30:33.165 --> 30:37.294
So keep your mouth shut,
or I'll shut it for you.

30:57.147 --> 30:58.940
[WIND GUSTS]
[SWORDS UNSHEATHE]

30:59.107 --> 31:00.150
LEON:
Is everyone all right?

31:00.317 --> 31:01.860
[SPEAKS MAGIC WORDS]

31:11.161 --> 31:12.788
Where's Lamia?

31:14.623 --> 31:16.166
Lamia!

31:40.440 --> 31:43.652
-What is this place?
-Whatever it is, it isn't safe.

31:44.111 --> 31:46.405
We need to find Lamia.
She could be in danger.

31:46.571 --> 31:50.784
We're the ones in danger, Leon.
She's brought us here to--

31:50.951 --> 31:53.036
-She's led us to a trap.
-That's a lie!

31:53.203 --> 31:55.080
She's poisoned your minds
and you can't see it.

31:55.247 --> 31:56.456
Enough!

31:56.623 --> 31:58.792
It was Lamia that attacked Elyan!

31:59.918 --> 32:03.296
| said enough!

32:03.463 --> 32:08.009
GWEN: Please! My brother's hurt.
We need to find him somewhere warm.

32:29.531 --> 32:31.241
Over here.

32:55.724 --> 32:58.351
-I'll make us a fire.
-Percival and I will search for Lamia.

33:01.062 --> 33:03.273
You will stay here
and you will do as Gwaine says.

33:03.440 --> 33:05.108
Do I make myself clear?

33:14.743 --> 33:17.454
It's impossible.
They can't have just disappeared.

33:17.621 --> 33:19.956
It could be that we're following
the wrong tracks, my lord.

33:20.123 --> 33:21.833
A number of people pass
through these woods.

33:22.000 --> 33:24.211
It was them. I know it was.

33:24.377 --> 33:26.588
Maybe we should go back to Longstead,
try in the morning.

33:26.755 --> 33:29.591
-By morning they could all be dead.
-They're knights of Camelot, my lord.

33:29.758 --> 33:32.636
-They're capable of looking after themselves.
-Maybe so.

33:32.802 --> 33:35.347
But you're forgetting one thing, uncle.
Guinevere is with them.

33:35.514 --> 33:37.349
- I realize that, sire.
-We keep going.

33:38.642 --> 33:39.726
All night if necessary.

33:49.903 --> 33:52.030
We need more wood.

33:52.864 --> 33:55.200
-I'll go and get some.
-Heh. No.

33:55.367 --> 33:58.828
You stay where you are. I'll get it myself.
You're not going anywhere.

33:58.995 --> 34:02.499
Gwaine, please listen to me.
It's not safe for you out there.

34:03.708 --> 34:06.127
-Are you trying to tell me my business?
-No. I'm just saying--

34:06.294 --> 34:08.672
-What?
-Nothing.

34:17.722 --> 34:21.601
If he doesn't get some help soon,
he's not going to make it.

34:27.732 --> 34:29.609
[HISSING NEARBY]

34:44.873 --> 34:46.626
[RUSTLING]

34:46.793 --> 34:48.920
[SQUEAKING]

35:00.932 --> 35:02.475
[HISSING]

35:02.642 --> 35:04.978
That was her. I'm sure of it.

35:05.145 --> 35:06.646
Lamia?

35:08.440 --> 35:10.108
It's nothing.

35:10.317 --> 35:12.235
[HISSING]

35:16.531 --> 35:19.451
| don't understand it.
Why have only the knights been enchanted?

35:19.618 --> 35:21.703
Why not us as well?

35:22.954 --> 35:25.457
-You're a woman.
-Soâ€?

35:26.291 --> 35:27.626
All her victims have been men.

35:28.668 --> 35:30.420
So why haven't you fallen under her spell?

35:33.298 --> 35:35.258
I've just been lucky, I suppose.

35:35.425 --> 35:38.470
-There must be a reason.
-Maybe it's because I'm not a knight.

35:38.637 --> 35:40.889
The three villagers weren't knights either.

35:41.056 --> 35:42.390
Who knows?

35:42.557 --> 35:44.517
There's something about you, Merlin.

35:45.226 --> 35:48.271
It's the way she looks at you,
as if you were the enemy.

35:48.730 --> 35:51.149
[MAN SCREAMS IN DISTANCE]

35:52.442 --> 35:54.986
Whatever you do, don't leave this room.

35:58.406 --> 36:00.659
[HISSING]

36:05.789 --> 36:07.582
[WHISPERING]
Gwaine.

36:19.511 --> 36:21.262
Gwaine.

36:36.861 --> 36:38.905
ARTHUR:
Agravaine.

36:39.072 --> 36:40.240
AGRAVAINE:
Huh?

36:40.407 --> 36:42.367
-It's Guinevere's.
-How can you be certain?

36:42.534 --> 36:46.579
It's from her tunic. I'd know it anywhere.
We must be close.

36:51.251 --> 36:53.002
[HISSING]

37:03.471 --> 37:04.848
Come on.

37:13.064 --> 37:15.108
[LAMIA WHIMPERING]

37:27.162 --> 37:28.955
[LAMIA SOBBING]

37:42.218 --> 37:43.428
Lamia.

37:56.775 --> 37:57.942
Are you all right?

37:58.902 --> 38:01.196
We've been looking everywhere for you.

38:01.696 --> 38:04.032
| thought you might never find me.

38:05.617 --> 38:07.660
Thank you, Percival.

38:09.037 --> 38:10.538
Thank you.

38:12.582 --> 38:14.292
[HISSING]

38:24.135 --> 38:25.637
No.

38:27.138 --> 38:28.807
No.

38:29.724 --> 38:32.143
No! No!

38:33.186 --> 38:34.562
[GRUNTING]

38:47.116 --> 38:48.785
[HISSING]

38:48.952 --> 38:50.703
You won't find me such easy prey.

38:54.082 --> 38:56.709
Your magic holds no fear for me.

38:57.085 --> 38:59.003
| could have killed you anytime I wished.

39:01.047 --> 39:03.842
Then what are you waiting for?

39:05.385 --> 39:07.136
[HISSING]

39:11.683 --> 39:13.351
[SPEAKS MAGIC WORDS]

39:14.394 --> 39:16.312
[GASPS]

39:23.945 --> 39:25.655
[LAMIA HISSING]

39:56.769 --> 39:58.104
[HISSING]

40:03.276 --> 40:04.485
[SPEAKS MAGIC WORDS]

40:20.710 --> 40:21.961
[SCREECHES]

40:23.004 --> 40:24.881
[RUMBLING]

40:37.268 --> 40:38.478
[PANTING]

40:38.686 --> 40:40.313
Merlin.

40:40.480 --> 40:42.023
[LAMIA HISSING]

40:59.624 --> 41:01.876
Get away from him!

41:03.962 --> 41:05.755
[SCREAMS]

41:16.891 --> 41:18.601
[SCREECHES]

41:19.686 --> 41:20.937
[GWEN PANTING]

41:27.193 --> 41:28.820
Arthur!

41:30.446 --> 41:33.116
You carry on. Don't worry about me.

41:34.742 --> 41:35.910
Sorry.

41:39.372 --> 41:40.456
[ARTHUR LAUGHS]

41:40.623 --> 41:42.125
It's almost good to see you, Merlin.

41:43.334 --> 41:45.545
-Likewise.
-Almost.

42:09.402 --> 42:10.987
How are they doing?

42:11.154 --> 42:14.365
| have given them the same compound
that cured the villagers, sire.

42:14.532 --> 42:17.744
They're fortunate that you got to them
when you did.

42:18.578 --> 42:20.204
Thank you, Gaius.

42:34.218 --> 42:37.555
So, Merlin.

42:37.972 --> 42:39.974
Being saved by a woman,
that really can't feel good.

42:41.768 --> 42:43.603
Feels a lot better than being dead.

42:43.770 --> 42:47.857
Does it? Being saved by a woman, or dying.

42:48.024 --> 42:50.276
-I'd have to think about that one.
-Don't think too hard.

42:50.443 --> 42:52.361
| wouldn't want you to hurt yourself.

42:57.450 --> 42:58.868
[BELL TOLLING]

43:00.745 --> 43:02.121
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

43:02.705 --> 43:04.082
Come.

43:07.210 --> 43:08.795
You wanted to see me?

43:08.961 --> 43:10.963
Just wanted to make sure you were all right.

43:11.130 --> 43:12.799
Been through a lot these past few days.

43:13.841 --> 43:15.259
I'm fine.

43:15.426 --> 43:17.804
Nothing a change of clothes couldn't cure.

43:18.387 --> 43:21.432
| thought I knew everything about you,
Guinevere.

43:22.266 --> 43:25.812
Your loyalty, your wisdom.

43:26.395 --> 43:28.147
Since when did you become
this fearless hero?

43:29.023 --> 43:31.317
Heh, well, maybe you just
didn't notice before.

43:31.484 --> 43:32.527
Hmm, maybe I didn't.

43:34.195 --> 43:35.613
Truly.

43:36.823 --> 43:38.324
You showed great courage back there.

43:39.867 --> 43:42.870
- I did what anyone else would have done.
-You did a good deal more than that.

43:43.037 --> 43:45.373
You were equal to any knight of Camelot.

43:45.790 --> 43:47.416
I'm proud of you.

43:48.334 --> 43:49.961
Really?

43:50.419 --> 43:52.046
Really.

43:59.554 --> 44:00.930
MALE VOICE:
Merlin.

44:01.139 --> 44:04.016
Guinevere, will you do me
the honor of becoming my wife?

44:05.810 --> 44:08.980
| want to believe that everything is fine,
that we really have Lancelot back.

44:12.358 --> 44:16.195
We can't thank you enough for what you
sacrificed on the Isle of the Blessed.

44:16.362 --> 44:17.947
[AUDIENCE CHEERING]

44:18.739 --> 44:20.199
Do you think he means to harm Arthur?

45:07.663 --> 45:09.665
[English - US - SDH]
